{"id":40,"parent_id":0,"book_id":22563,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":40,"title":"“Whatsoever a Man Soweth, That Shall He Also Reap”","subtitle":"","short_title":38,"uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap","content":[["div",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.head1"},[".titleNumber","38"],["h1","“Whatsoever a Man Soweth, That Shall He Also Reap”"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Theme"],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p4"},"Only those who endure in righteousness unto the end will receive eternal life."]],[".topic",["h2","Theme Analysis"],["div",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.f1"},["ul.content-list alphaCaps",["li",["span.label","A."],["div",[".para","The law of the harvest is that one reaps as he sows."]]],["li",["span.label","B."],["div",[".para","The gospel of Jesus Christ provides that the child of God may bring forth an abundant harvest—even an hundred fold."]]],["li",["span.label","C."],["div",[".para","God is not mocked; thus, ultimately, only the faithful will eat the good of the land."]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Study Sources"],[".topic",["h3","New Testament Reading Assignment"],["div",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p11"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/1"},"Galatians 1-6"]]],[".topic",["h3","Course Manual"],["div",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p13"},"Chapter 38, “Whatsoever a Man Soweth, That Shall He Also Reap”"]],[".topic",["h3","Standard Works"],["div",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p15"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/5.16-26"},"Galatians 5:16-26"],". How can we identify whether or not we are bringing forth good fruit?"],["div",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/6.7-9"},"Galatians 6:7-9"],". What is the law of the harvest?"],["div",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p17"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/13.8,23"},"Matthew 13:8, 23"],". On what principles does one bring forth good fruit?"],["div",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/32.42"},"Alma 32:42"],". Why is it that many never reap a good harvest in their lives?"],["div",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p19"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/15.1-8"},"John 15:1-8"],". What is the key to bringing forth fruit unto perfection?"],["div",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/mal/4.1"},"Malachi 4:1"],". How fruitful are the wicked?"],["div",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p21"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/5.47"},"Jacob 5:47"],". How does the Lord help his children to be fruitful?"],["div",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/1.1-3"},"Psalms 1:1-3"],". How can one repent and become fruitful?",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/41.1-10"},"Alma 41:1-10"],". What is the law of restoration?"]],[".topic",["h3","Basic Library"],["div",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p24"},["span.emphasis","Teachings,"],"p. 365. The doctrine of judgment is a primary principle of the gospel. It will be a harvest."],["div",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p25"},["span.emphasis","M of F,"],"pp. 301-22. The time of harvest will be a day of reckoning."],["div",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p26"},["span.emphasis","DS,"],"3:14-18. The great harvest of the last days."],["div",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p27"},"Spencer W. Kimball in",["span.emphasis","CR,"],"Oct. 1970, pp. 68-72. Years the locust hath eaten—opportunities misused."],["div",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p28"},["span.emphasis","Jesus the Christ,"],"pp. 576-86. Three parables on the law of the harvest."]],[".topic",["h3","Additional Sources"],["div",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p30"},"Sterling W. Sill,",["span.emphasis","The Law of the Harvest,"],"pp. 11-18. What is the law of the harvest?"],["div",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p31"},"John H. Vandenberg in",["span.emphasis","CR,"],"Oct. 1968, pp, 31-34. Harvest in human life."]]],[".topic",["h2","Some Suggestions for Presentation"],[".subtitle","(Ideas Other Teachers Have Used)"],[".topic",["h3","Years the Locust Hath Eaten (A Discussion)"],["div",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.f2"},"The instructor could promote an interesting discussion around President Kimball’s conference talk (see basic library sources) and might ask some of the following questions:",["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","What happens when one rejects Church calls?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","How might one reap the whirlwind of an unsuccessful marriage?"]],["li",["span.label","3."],[".para","How are children the harvest of the Lord?"]],["li",["span.label","4."],[".para","How important are our opportunities?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3","Are We Pleasant Plants unto the Lord? (A Discussion)"],["div",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.f3"},"By asking the following questions, the instructor could encourage a significant discussion:",["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","What constitutes the vineyard of the Lord? Who are his pleasant plants? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/5.7"},"Isaiah 5:7"],".)"]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","What does the Lord expect of his children? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/3.10"},"Matthew 3:10"],".)"]],["li",["span.label","3."],[".para","list some specific ways that one can be fruitful unto the Lord and bring forth a bounteous harvest. (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/32.37-43"},"Alma 32:37-43"],".)"]],["li",["span.label","4."],[".para","What happens to the tree that will not bring forth good fruit? (See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/5.46"},"Jacob 5:46"],".)"]]]]],[".topic",["h3","The Law of Restoration (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/40"},"Alma 40, 41"],") (An Illustration)"],["div",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p47"},"In attempting to explain the Lord’s law of justice to his son Corianton, Alma articulated the law of restoration. This could be illustrated thusly:"]],[".topic",["h3","The Sum Total of One’s Acts—That Which Has Been Sown"],[".",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.f4"}]],[".topic",["h3","The Law of Moses and the Traditions of Men (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/3.24"},"Galatians 3:24"],") (An Illustration)"],["div",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/whatsoever-a-man-soweth-that-shall-he-also-reap.p57"},"See transparency 12, The Law of Moses."]]]]],"refs":null}
